The paper addresses the topic of knowledge graph embedding, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper proposes a novel Gaussian mixture model for embedding, which falls under the category of generative models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves learning continuous vector representations of entities and relations, which falls under the category of machine learning and specifically, deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing and semantic analysis, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves database management and querying, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval and search, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
